    "financials": "OP Group's financial performance is strong, benefiting from dominant Finnish market share and a diversified revenue base (banking + insurance). The cooperative model means profits are partially returned to owner-members as bonuses, which drives customer loyalty. Net interest income is supported by the large mortgage portfolio. Insurance operations provide diversification. The group maintains strong capital ratios and low credit losses, reflecting conservative Finnish lending practices.",
    "digital_strategy": "OP has been a digital innovation leader in Finland. The OP Mobile app is highly rated and widely used. OP launched OP Light for younger customers — a simplified digital banking experience. The group has invested in AI-driven personalization, automated lending decisions, and digital insurance integration. The cooperative structure creates a unique digital challenge: providing a unified digital platform across 120+ independently governed member banks, each with their own local identity but needing consistent technology. This is exactly the kind of multi-entity digital platform challenge that few vendors can address.",
    "strategic_initiatives": "Key priorities: (1) Unified digital platform across all 120+ member cooperatives, (2) Insurance-banking integration to create seamless financial services, (3) AI and data analytics for personalization, (4) SME and entrepreneurial banking growth, (5) Wealth management expansion, (6) Operational efficiency through shared services automation.",
    "acquisitions_partnerships": "OP Group has grown primarily through member bank mergers (consolidation of smaller cooperatives into larger units). Technology investments have been largely in-house, but the scale of digital transformation across 120+ entities creates interest in platform solutions. OP has been exploring partnerships for specific capabilities.",
